cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper presents a Python package that combines XGBoost with weighted and focal losses to tackle binary label-imbalanced classification tasks. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on machine learning and classification tasks, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV.
